      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1) is a commercially validated code with documented version control, regression test suite, and user access controls. SQA documentation satisfies Gradation 2 requirements: version-controlled input files, documented solver settings, and traceable run logs are maintained in the project repository. No deficiencies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification was performed using method-of-manufactured solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. Observed order of convergence (p=1.94) is consistent with the nominal second-order spatial accuracy. Residual convergence to 1e-6 confirmed for all operating points. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted following the GCI methodology (Celik et al. 2008). The fine-grid GCI for the primary QoI (volume-averaged shear stress scalar) is 4.8%, which exceeds the Gradation 2 threshold of ≤3% established in the acceptance criteria. The medium mesh was selected for production runs due to computational resource constraints. The GCI on the hemolysis index itself reaches 7.2% at the highest-flow operating point, indicating that discretization uncertainty is a non-negligible contributor to total model uncertainty. This factor achieves only Gradation 1 — below the required Gradation 2 — and constitutes a primary basis for the Not Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) were documented in the experimental protocol and confirmed to match the five CFD operating points within ±2% for all parameters. Fluid rheology (non-Newtonian Carreau model) parameters were derived from the same blood lot used in experiments. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) was compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute relative error is 9.3% across the operating range, within the Gradation 2 acceptance band of ≤15%. Uncertainty in experimental measurements (CV=6.1%) was accounted for in the comparison metric. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — relative hemolysis index RH computed from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage model — is directly relevant to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) are physically linked to hemolysis mechanisms. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares the impeller topology of the subject device but differs in volute geometry and clearance gaps. The operating range of the validation dataset (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) partially covers the COU operating envelope but does not include the highest-flow, highest-speed corner point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM) identified as the candidate worst-case condition. This gap in validation coverage means the model's predictive accuracy is unconfirmed at the most safety-critical operating point. Extrapolation uncertainty is unquantified. This factor achieves only Gradation 1 — below the required Gradation 2 — and constitutes a co-primary basis for the Not Accepted decision alongside the discretization error finding."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 with Medium model influence, numerical solver error beyond code verification and discretization error assessment is scoped out per the ASME V&V 40 factor applicability table. The commercial solver's iterative convergence is monitored via residual tracking; no iterative solver error contribution is identified as a significant uncertainty source for this steady-state RANS application."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is scoped out at MRL 2 per the factor applicability matrix. All simulation inputs were reviewed by a second analyst and discrepancies resolved prior to production runs. Documented peer-review process satisfies the Gradation 1 threshold applicable at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model selection, hemolysis damage model) is scoped out at MRL 2 per the factor applicability table. The SST k-ω turbulence model is the community-accepted standard for internal blood-flow CFD (FDA Critical Path). The Giersiepen-Wurzinger damage model is the regulatory precedent model. Gradation 1 satisfied by documented model selection rationale."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl2",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (geometry dimensions, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are traceable to measurement records or published material data. Geometric dimensions were measured from the physical prototype with documented uncertainty (±0.05 mm). Sensitivity analysis confirmed that dimensional tolerances produce less than 2% variation in the hemolysis index at nominal operating conditions. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
