  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-cpb-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cfd-lab-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis worst-case identification, MRL 2) concludes Not Accepted based on two factors that fail to meet their required Gradation 2 levels. (1) Discretization Error: The fine-grid GCI for the hemolysis index QoI is 7.2% at the highest-flow operating point, exceeding the ≤3% threshold established in the acceptance criteria for Gradation 2. Only the medium mesh was used in production runs; refining to the fine mesh was not completed. This factor achieves Gradation 1 only. (2) Relevance of Validation Activities to the COU: The validation dataset does not cover the 6 L/min / 3500 RPM operating point, which is the candidate worst-case condition for the COU decision. Model accuracy at this safety-critical corner is undemonstrated, and extrapolation uncertainty is unquantified. This factor achieves Gradation 1 only. Both deficiencies are marginal in isolation — the overall model performs well across the covered operating range — but together they leave the model's predictive credibility unestablished at the specific condition most relevant to the regulatory decision. The Not Accepted decision is consistent with the ASME V&V 40 framework requirement that all assessed factors meet or exceed required levels before a positive credibility finding can be issued. A path to Accepted exists: (a) complete fine-mesh production runs and confirm GCI ≤3%, and (b) conduct supplemental bench validation at the 6 L/min / 3500 RPM operating point. No safety concerns preclude resubmission following these targeted activities.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
